# Release Workflow

- Maintain two separate update paths: `experimental` (testing) and `main` (stable user path).
- Assume routine changes should be pushed to `experimental` without requiring per-change confirmation.
- Push to `main` only when explicitly instructed.
- When promoting changes to `main`, ensure all intended `experimental` updates are carried over safely.
- Preserve the separation so both update paths continue to work independently.
